  "ai_usage": "Use for any button that triggers async work (submit, save, pay). On action: add the loading class, set button.disabled=true and aria-busy='true', swap label for a spinner; on resolve/reject, revert and optionally show success/error. Reserve a fixed min-width so the button doesn't resize. NEVER leave it stuck loading — always restore on both success and failure paths. The demo auto-toggles to show both states.",
  "path": "effects/buttons/loading-button.html",
  "source": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>Loading Button</title>\n  <script type=\"application/json\" id=\"effect-meta\">\n  {\n    \"id\": \"loading-button\",\n    \"title\": \"Loading Button\",\n    \"summary\": \"A submit button that swaps its label for an inline spinner and locks during async work.\",\n    \"description\": \"Toggling a loading state hides the label, shows a spinner, disables the button, and sets aria-busy — the correct pattern for form submits and async actions.\",\n    \"theme\": \"buttons\",\n    \"categories\": [\"button\", \"loading\", \"feedback\"],\n    \"tags\": [\"loading\", \"spinner\", \"submit\", \"async\", \"disabled\", \"aria-busy\"],\n    \"tech\": [\"css\", \"js\"],\n    \"era\": \"2020s\",\n    \"difficulty\": \"beginner\",\n    \"dependencies\": [],\n    \"browser_support\": \"All browsers.\",\n    \"performance_notes\": \"One spinner rotation while loading; trivial.\",\n    \"accessibility_notes\": \"Set disabled + aria-busy='true' during loading so it can't be double-submitted and assistive tech knows it's working. Keep the button width stable to avoid layout shift. Restore state on completion/error.\",\n    \"customization\": [\n      { \"name\": \"--bg\", \"description\": \"Button color\", \"default\": \"#7c5cff\" }\n    ],\n    \"variations\": [\"Success checkmark on completion\", \"Progress percentage label\", \"Disable the whole form during submit\"],\n    \"related\": [\"ring-spinner\", \"glow-pulse-button\"],\n    \"ai_usage\": \"Use for any button that triggers async work (submit, save, pay). On action: add the loading class, set button.disabled=true and aria-busy='true', swap label for a spinner; on resolve/reject, revert and optionally show success/error. Reserve a fixed min-width so the button doesn't resize. NEVER leave it stuck loading — always restore on both success and failure paths. The demo auto-toggles to show both states.\"\n  }\n  </script>\n  <style>\n    :root { --bg: #7c5cff; }\n    html, body { height: 100%; margin: 0; }\n    body { display: grid; place-items: center; background: #0b0d12; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }\n    .load-btn {\n      position: relative; min-width: 160px; border: none; cursor: pointer; color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem;\n      padding: .85rem 1.6rem; border-radius: 12px; background: var(--bg);\n    }\n    .load-btn[disabled] { cursor: progress; opacity: .85; }\n    .load-btn .label { transition: opacity .15s; }\n    .load-btn.loading .label { opacity: 0; }\n    .load-btn .spin {\n      position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%; width: 18px; height: 18px; margin: -9px 0 0 -9px; opacity: 0;\n      border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,.4); border-top-color: #fff; border-radius: 50%;\n    }\n    .load-btn.loading .spin { opacity: 1; animation: spin .8s linear infinite; }\n    @keyframes spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }\n    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { .load-btn.loading .spin { animation-duration: 2s; } }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <button class=\"load-btn\" id=\"btn\"><span class=\"label\">Save changes</span><span class=\"spin\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n  <script>\n    var btn = document.getElementById(\"btn\");\n    function setLoading(on) {\n      btn.classList.toggle(\"loading\", on);\n      btn.disabled = on; btn.setAttribute(\"aria-busy\", String(on));\n    }\n    btn.addEventListener(\"click\", function () { setLoading(true); setTimeout(function () { setLoading(false); }, 1800); });\n    // Auto-demo so both states are visible in the catalog frame.\n    setInterval(function () { if (!btn.classList.contains(\"loading\")) { setLoading(true); setTimeout(function () { setLoading(false); }, 1800); } }, 3600);\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>\n"
}
